Fuse ZX Spectrum emulator - per-name tape autosave
==================================================

What it does
    Makes SAVE "name" write a standalone tape file to $FUSE_SAVE_DIR/name.tzx
    (one program per file), written atomically (temp file + rename) so a power
    loss mid-save cannot corrupt an existing file. LOAD is unaffected.
    Inert unless the environment variable FUSE_SAVE_DIR is set.

Target
    Fuse source tree, file: tape.c (function tape_save_trap).
    Written against Fuse 1.8.0 / current source.

How to apply (from inside the unpacked Fuse source directory)
    cd fuse-1.8.0
    patch -p0 < /path/to/fuse-savehook.patch

    Then build as usual:
    ./configure --without-gtk --with-sdl && make && sudo make install

    Minor "offset"/"fuzz" messages from patch are fine; only a "FAILED"/
    "*.rej" file means the source differs too much - re-cut against your tape.c.

How to reverse
    cd fuse-1.8.0
    patch -R -p0 < /path/to/fuse-savehook.patch

Runtime
    Launch Fuse with the target directory exported, e.g.:
    FUSE_SAVE_DIR="$HOME/tapes" fuse --full-screen --no-statusbar

